  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Combatting Sexual and Gende based violence - RCBIF</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is expected that each of these activities will contribute significantly toward the transformation of policies, which in turn will lead to a more favourable climate for a change in cultural norms and attitudes toward the prevention of SGBV. By building and maintaining existing partnerships and networks across multiple sectors this programme intends to ensure survivors safely access legal system, medical and psychological services, as well as police and other support services. Christian Aid will also be working with RCBIF to establish and build the capacity of local community support systems to help keep survivors safe from further violence</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intends to advocate for the implementation of public policies and laws to end sexual gender-based violence, to influence and change the social norms that condone violence, and to support survivors through quality care</narrative>
  </description>
